org.xflatdb.xflat.db

Class TimestampIdGenerator

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.xflatdb.xflat.db.IdGenerator
      • org.xflatdb.xflat.db.TimestampIdGenerator

  • public class TimestampIdGenerator
extends IdGenerator
    An ID Generator that generates timestamp based IDs. The timestamps are stored as ISO date strings. To uniqueify the ID, the millisecond is incremented. Do not use this ID generator in insert-heavy tables that may need more than 1000 dates per second.
    Author:
    gordon

        public boolean supports(Class<?> idType)
        Description copied from class: IdGenerator
        Indicates whether the given ID property type is supported by this ID generator. If false, then IDs generated by this generator cannot be assigned to the ID property of the POJO, and thus the POJO cannot be stored in this Table.
        Specified by:

      • saveState

        public void saveState(org.jdom2.Element state)
        Description copied from class: IdGenerator
        Saves this ID generator's state to a JDOM Element so it can save when its associated Engine spins down. When saving state the IdGenerator is guaranteed to have no invocations on IdGenerator.generateNewId(java.lang.Class<?>). Stateless ID generators such as the UuidIdGenerator do not have to override this.
        Overrides:
        saveState in class IdGenerator
        Parameters:
        state - The table metadata element to which the IdGenerator should save any state info.
